(6,1,"2019-09-10 02:04:37","2019-09-10 02:04:37","<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaId\":92,\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://muslim-therapy.local/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Raumene.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-92\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\n\nRaumene Rahatzad is a Licensed Professional Counselor offering in-person counseling services in the greater Portland, OR metropolitan area, and phone and video counseling throughout the state of Oregon (nationally and internationally?). \n\n</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Raumene also provides presentations and workshops to community counseling centers, hospitals, schools, religious organizations, companies, and other groups.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3> Experience</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Raumene has over 5 years of counseling experience working with individuals, couples, families and groups at a regional community health organization that serves a diverse set of clients. He has extensive experience supporting people through trauma and recovery, overcoming anxiety and depression, improving relationships, developing self-knowledge and awareness, navigating complex cultural issues, nurturing faith, facilitating spiritual growth, and more. Raumene’s travels abroad, education, and life experiences have further enhanced his ability to connect with people from all walks of life.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4>EDUCATION</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"className\":\"about-list\"} -->\n<ul class=\"about-list\"><li> Master’s of Science in Counseling (MS)</li><li> Focus: Couples and Family Counseling</li><li> Portland State University, 2014</li><li> Bachelor of Arts in International and Intercultural Studies (BA)</li><li> Focus: Middle East</li><li> Pitzer College, 2006</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4><br> LICENSES, CERTIFICATIONS, and TRAINING</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"className\":\"about-list\"} -->\n<ul class=\"about-list\"><li> Licensed Professional Counselor (LPC)</li><li> National Board Certified Counselor (NBCC)</li><li> Oregon Board of Licensed Professional Counselors and Therapists</li><li> EMDR Trained Counselor</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4> PROFESSIONAL MEMBERSHIPS</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"className\":\"about-list\"} -->\n<ul class=\"about-list\"><li>International Association of Islamic Psychology - Associate Fellow</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Approach</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Raumene has an integrative approach to counseling that is rooted in Islamic psychology and utilizes components of cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT), dialectical behavior therapy (DBT), eye movement and desensitization and reprocessing (EMDR), emotionally focused therapy (EFT), mindfulness practice, and other modalities to best serve your goals. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Raumene believes in creating a safe, non-judgmental and compassionate space where he can work with you on your therapeutic goals. He believes the counseling relationship can serve as a center to explore new ways of thinking, behaving, and relating to others. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Raumene believes that the heart is the core of our being. This faculty is not limited to only the physical heart, but includes a spiritual dimension. The heart is our greatest source of connection to The Divine and has its own unique way of feeling, knowing, and processing. When our hearts are sick we suffer, and when are hearts are sound we thrive. Raumene focuses on heartwork, while integrating all aspects of the human experience, to<br> support people in attaining hope, healing, and transformation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>“Truly in the body is a piece of flesh, if it is sound the entire body is sound and if it is corrupt the entire body is corrupt, truly it is the heart.”</p><cite>  ~ Prophet Muhammad (peace and blessings of God be upon him) </cite></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->","About","","publish","closed","closed","","about","","","2019-09-11 04:47:40","2019-09-11 04:47:40","",0,"http://muslim-therapy.local/?page_id=6",0,"page","",0),
