(15,1,"2019-09-10 02:06:14","2019-09-10 02:06:14","<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>1) Q: What is counseling?<br>    A: Counseling is… </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> 2) What is Islamic psychology?<br>  A: Islamic psychology is </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> 3) Can I benefit from these services if I’m not Muslim?<br> A: Yes, absolutely. My theoretical orientation is rooted in Islamic psychology, which means my understanding of the human being comes from the Islamic tradition. I believe all people can benefit from what the Islamic tradition has to offer on matters related to the intellect, the heart, and the spirit; similar to the same way “mindfulness” from the Buddhist tradition has benefited people of all beliefs. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> 4) Can I benefit from services if I’m not religious or spiritual?<br> A: Yes. I have experience using CBT, DBT, EMDR, emotionally focused, and other modalities and interventions to help all people feel better and reduce anxiety, depression, PTSD symptoms, relationship challenges, and more. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":121} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://muslim-therapy.local/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/t-foz-3NLPLfoLM3I-unsplash-1024x683.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-121\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>RATES</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Individual Counseling: The standard rate is <strong>$120 per hour</strong>. A sliding scale rate of <strong>$40-$120</strong> is available for individuals who have financial need. Couples and Family Counseling: The standard rate is <strong>$150 per hour</strong>. A sliding scale rate of <strong>$60 - $150</strong> is available for couples and families who have financial need.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Group Counseling: <strong>$35.00 per hour</strong>, per person.</p>